FBIS3-31930 "drlat020_g_94007" FBIS-LAT-94-020 Document Type:Daily Report 31 Jan 1994 Guatemala Police Deployed at National Palace To Prevent Disturbances PA2801193194 Guatemala City Cadena de Emisoras Unidas in Spanish 1828 GMT 28 Jan 94 PA2801193194 Guatemala City Cadena de Emisoras Unidas Language: Spanish Article Type:BFN [Text] Strong security measures have been taken around the National Palace to prevent any confrontation with the peasants who are marching to the central plaza. Approximately 200 policemen have been deployed in the capital's downtown area to prevent violence by demonstrators and infiltrators. The decorative streetlights outside the National Palace have been removed to keep them from being damaged if disturbances break out. Here is a report by Ana Julieta Cardenas. [Begin recording] [Cardenas] It was reported from the National Palace that there is normal activity around the area despite increased security by National Police personnel and soldiers who regularly guard the building. People are entering and leaving the building without any problem. The government minister has said that the security troops are on alert to forestall any possible disturbances. He is going to report on the reaction by government offices to the strike announced by the workers. [Government Minister Arnoldo Ortiz] [Words indistinct] on the strike that was announced [words indistinct] study on economy reveals it is totally normal. Communications are totally normal. Postal service is completely normal. Everything appears normal in the capital. [Words indistinct] everything is reported to be normal. [Words indistinct] first appearance was that there was strike announced. [end recording]
